00:47:30.035 --> 00:47:31.410
what about this,
what about that?

00:47:31.410 --> 00:47:35.100
Because this is still a
subject which is picked over.

00:47:35.100 --> 00:47:37.440
So Charles Bennett,
who in my view

00:47:37.440 --> 00:47:40.950
settled it to my satisfaction,
has his detractors that say,

00:47:40.950 --> 00:47:44.370
but what about if you did
this, and supposing that?

00:47:44.370 --> 00:47:49.650
But I think overall, the key
message is that it's not the--

00:47:49.650 --> 00:47:52.492
Szilard thought it was
the act of acquisition

00:47:52.492 --> 00:47:54.450
of the information, that
in order for the demon

00:47:54.450 --> 00:47:56.240
to know what the
molecules were doing

00:47:56.240 --> 00:47:58.033
would have to expend energy.

00:47:58.033 --> 00:47:59.700
And that energy would
raise the entropy,

00:47:59.700 --> 00:48:01.470
and that's where
the books balance.

00:48:01.470 --> 00:48:02.980
It wasn't at that stage.

00:48:02.980 --> 00:48:05.100
It's at the clearing
of the register stage.

00:48:05.100 --> 00:48:06.930
So it really is--

00:48:06.930 --> 00:48:09.570
this is where thermodynamics
and computing really

00:48:09.570 --> 00:48:10.890
do mesh together.

00:48:10.890 --> 00:48:14.130
Because it's not the
physics of sensing.

00:48:14.130 --> 00:48:17.050
It's the physics of computation
that saves the second law.

00:48:17.050 --> 00:48:19.050
So there's very,
very deep connection

00:48:19.050 --> 00:48:23.070
between the world of computing
and life, which I think

00:48:23.070 --> 00:48:25.830
is sort of increasingly
obvious to everybody.

00:48:25.830 --> 00:48:28.260
Here we see it boiled
down to it's essentials

00:48:28.260 --> 00:48:31.200
in Szilard's Engine and
Bennett's resolution

00:48:31.200 --> 00:48:33.372
of the demon paradox.

