00:49:05.010 --> 00:49:10.455
in the book, let me
just cut to the chase

00:49:10.455 --> 00:49:12.320
and tell you my own
position on free will.

00:49:12.320 --> 00:49:15.510
Free will, I think, is
a feeling that we have.

00:49:15.510 --> 00:49:19.200
More to the point, and
this comes out in the book,

00:49:19.200 --> 00:49:23.010
that free will is closely
connected to our sense

00:49:23.010 --> 00:49:25.610
that time is flowing.

00:49:25.610 --> 00:49:27.870
Now, a physicist will
tell you time can't flow.

00:49:27.870 --> 00:49:30.560
That's an illusion, but it's
a necessary illusion for us

00:49:30.560 --> 00:49:31.800
to live our lives.

00:49:31.800 --> 00:49:34.440
We live our lives
as if time flows.

00:49:34.440 --> 00:49:36.376
It doesn't flow.

00:49:36.376 --> 00:49:38.590
There are simply intervals
between events and states

00:49:38.590 --> 00:49:39.980
of your brain.

00:49:39.980 --> 00:49:42.910
So I think that the
illusion of the flow of time

00:49:42.910 --> 00:49:46.690
is because we convince
ourselves that we have--

00:49:46.690 --> 00:49:50.040
I have to use the word, we
have selves, conserved selves,

00:49:50.040 --> 00:49:53.983
that I'm the same self as
I had when I was a child.

00:49:53.983 --> 00:49:55.900
In other words, that the
self stays unchanged,

00:49:55.900 --> 00:49:57.950
and the world changes around us.

00:49:57.950 --> 00:49:59.950
That gives us an impression
of the flow of time.

00:49:59.950 --> 00:50:02.200
I think that's back to front.

00:50:02.200 --> 00:50:04.770
I think the world
doesn't change.

00:50:04.770 --> 00:50:06.280
There are simply
successive states.

00:50:06.280 --> 00:50:09.540
Time isn't flowing, but
at each successive moment,

00:50:09.540 --> 00:50:12.110
you're a slightly different
self from what you were before.

00:50:12.110 --> 00:50:14.290
So a lot of mutual information
between today's self

00:50:14.290 --> 00:50:16.910
and yesterday's self,
but it is different.

00:50:16.910 --> 00:50:20.180
You're a different person today
from what you were yesterday.

00:50:20.180 --> 00:50:22.540
So I think our sense of
freedom has to do with getting

00:50:22.540 --> 00:50:24.430
that back to front.

00:50:24.430 --> 00:50:25.510
Anyway, read the book.

00:50:28.270 --> 00:50:32.650
AUDIENCE: On the last slide on
quantum computation and quantum

00:50:32.650 --> 00:50:38.590
biology and the link, are any
proposals for a physical system

00:50:38.590 --> 00:50:42.970
that, inside biology, could
do useful quantum computation

00:50:42.970 --> 00:50:45.070
in the sense that
how will a qubit

00:50:45.070 --> 00:50:47.470
or coherence of a qubit
or a a bunch of qubits

00:50:47.470 --> 00:50:49.540
be maintained in a--

00:50:49.540 --> 00:50:50.900
temperature, moisture, etc.

00:50:50.900 --> 00:50:52.130
PAUL DAVIES: Right No,
no, that's all right.

00:50:52.130 --> 00:50:54.380
So first of all, that's the
biggest subject in quantum

00:50:54.380 --> 00:50:55.450
biology generally.

00:50:55.450 --> 00:50:58.900
Can biology deploy
any quantum effects

00:50:58.900 --> 00:51:00.790
involving things
like entanglement

00:51:00.790 --> 00:51:02.200
and tunneling and so on?

00:51:02.200 --> 00:51:05.170
The answer to that is,
almost certainly yes.

00:51:05.170 --> 00:51:08.920
And I give four examples in that
particular chapter in the book,

00:51:08.920 --> 00:51:11.770
while having to do
with in photosynthesis

00:51:11.770 --> 00:51:14.950
the transfer of energy
from the light harvesting

00:51:14.950 --> 00:51:18.260
center to the chemical
reaction center.

00:51:18.260 --> 00:51:19.990
Now that has to do
with bird navigation,

00:51:19.990 --> 00:51:24.890
extraordinary thing,
olfactory response of flies,

00:51:24.890 --> 00:51:26.740
and some other things in there.

00:51:26.740 --> 00:51:29.810
The one that really strikes me,
because my colleagues at ASU

00:51:29.810 --> 00:51:31.780
are doing experiments,
is the way

00:51:31.780 --> 00:51:35.140
that electron tunneling
through organic molecules

00:51:35.140 --> 00:51:38.090
can be dramatically different
according to the sequence,

00:51:38.090 --> 00:51:40.810
say, if it's a protein,
the nucleotide sequence.

00:51:40.810 --> 00:51:43.720
A colleague of mine said,
change one amino acid,

00:51:43.720 --> 00:51:45.220
and it's like an on/off switch.

00:51:45.220 --> 00:51:49.000
So it looks like
biology has fine tuned,

00:51:49.000 --> 00:51:52.660
by natural selection, fine
tuned these organically

00:51:52.660 --> 00:51:55.890
functional molecules to have
special quantum tunneling

00:51:55.890 --> 00:51:56.390
properties.

00:51:56.390 --> 00:51:57.890
So I think there's
very little doubt

00:51:57.890 --> 00:52:01.600
that quantum mechanics is
playing a role in biology.

00:52:01.600 --> 00:52:03.910
What's not clear is
whether this is just

00:52:03.910 --> 00:52:07.960
a few quirky little
things that life

00:52:07.960 --> 00:52:09.880
has stumbled across
and taken advantage of,

00:52:09.880 --> 00:52:12.940
or whether it's the tip
of a quantum iceberg.

00:52:12.940 --> 00:52:15.560
But your question
specifically was,

00:52:15.560 --> 00:52:17.620
can there be qubit processing?

00:52:17.620 --> 00:52:21.880
There was a claim by
Apoorva Patel from India

00:52:21.880 --> 00:52:24.610
that that indeed
was taking place,

00:52:24.610 --> 00:52:28.300
that it was actually Grover's
Algorithm being implemented

00:52:28.300 --> 00:52:29.980
in the genetic code.

00:52:29.980 --> 00:52:33.092
He's backed away from that
claim in recent years.

00:52:33.092 --> 00:52:34.300
So it was a sort of nice try.

00:52:34.300 --> 00:52:36.040
It gained a lot of attention.

00:52:36.040 --> 00:52:36.890
I agree with you.

00:52:36.890 --> 00:52:38.348
In that warm, wet
environment, it's

00:52:38.348 --> 00:52:42.257
very hard to see how decoherence
wouldn't kill this stone dead.

00:52:42.257 --> 00:52:44.590
But that would also be true
of some of the other quantum

00:52:44.590 --> 00:52:45.170
effects.

00:52:45.170 --> 00:52:47.770
And again, there's
a lot of work being

00:52:47.770 --> 00:52:51.580
done to see how the
quantum processes could

00:52:51.580 --> 00:52:54.850
be screened, could screen
out the environmental noise,

00:52:54.850 --> 00:52:56.170
and so on.

00:52:56.170 --> 00:52:58.210
And so it could be
that biology has

00:52:58.210 --> 00:53:00.190
got a trick or two
to teach people

00:53:00.190 --> 00:53:01.610
working in quantum computing.

00:53:01.610 --> 00:53:02.985
There's certainly
some people who

00:53:02.985 --> 00:53:05.960
do work in quantum computing
who are aware of this.

00:53:05.960 --> 00:53:08.770
But this is all very
much the cutting edge.

00:53:08.770 --> 00:53:10.850
I think we'll find out
in the coming years.

